TY  - JOUR
TI  - An Intertemporal General Equilibrium Model of Asset Prices
AU  - Cox, John C.
AU  - Ingersoll, Jonathan E.
AU  - Ross, Stephen A.
AB  - [This paper develops a continuous time general equilibrium model of a simple but complete economy and uses it to examine the behavior of asset prices. In this model, asset prices and their stochastic properties are determined endogenously. One principal result is a partial differential equation which asset prices must satisfy. The solution of this equation gives the equilibrium price of any asset in terms of the underlying real variables in the economy.]
